cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with training neural networks to be adversarially robust. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments were conducted on the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is a popular dataset for image classification tasks. 

Furthermore, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with defending against adversarial attacks on neural networks. 

It may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the robustness of neural networks. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks and their training.
